    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemongrass-pork-burger-and-sweet-chilli-chips/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Bash your <strong>lemongrass</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong>, remove the <strong>tough outer layer[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and discard, then chop the <strong>softer inner core[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Peel your <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>shallot[s]</strong> and chop in half</p><p>Strip your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems, discard the stems</p><p>Add the <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>shallot halves</strong>, <strong>lemongrass</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the <strong>mint leaves </strong>and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>coriander</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to a <strong>food processor</strong> and blitz until finely chopped \u2013 this is your <strong>lemongrass</strong> <strong>paste</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemongrass-pork-burger-and-sweet-chilli-chips/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once blitzed, combine the<strong> lemongrass paste</strong>,<strong> mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) and <strong>soy sauce</strong> in a large bowl and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>lemongrass mince</strong></p><p>Divide the <strong>lemongrass mince</strong> and shape into one burger patty per person</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemongrass-pork-burger-and-sweet-chilli-chips/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> lemongrass patty[ies]</strong>, press it down firmly with a spatula and cook for 5 min</p><p>Reduce the heat to medium-high, flip the <strong>patty[ies]</strong> and cook for a further 5 min or until charred and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemongrass-pork-burger-and-sweet-chilli-chips/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the patty[ies] is cooking, peel your <strong>carrot[s]</strong>, then continue to peel lengths until you end up with a pile of carrot ribbons</p><p>Add the <strong>carrot ribbons</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>rice vinegar </strong>and give everything a good mix up and set aside \u2013 these are your <strong>quick-pickled carrot ribbons</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemongrass-pork-burger-and-sweet-chilli-chips/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> to a baking tray (cut side up) and put the tray in the oven for 5 min or until they're hot and crusty</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemongrass-pork-burger-and-sweet-chilli-chips/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>red chilli</strong> <strong>relish</strong> and <strong>mayo </strong>in a small bowl<strong> </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> sweet chilli mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemongrass-pork-burger-and-sweet-chilli-chips/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the base of the <strong>toasted ciabatta</strong> with some <strong>sweet chilli mayo</strong>, the <strong>remaining coriander </strong>and <strong>mint</strong>, a<strong> lemongrass patty </strong>and the <strong>quick-pickled carrot ribbons</strong> then top with the <strong>ciabatta lid</strong></p><p>Serve with the <strong>chips</strong> to the side and drizzle over the <strong>remaining sweet chilli mayo</strong>, then top with the <strong>chopped spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
